        "id": 4769,
        "name": "",
        "username": "Sraw",
        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/s/a88e57/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2019-08-01T08:33:44.154Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Hi, first very thanks for your detail explaination! But I still have confusion about <code>kvranges</code>.</p>\n<p>For the example, so the <code>kvranges</code> is written in 10 days? What kind of data is written in these 10 days? Do you mean the cluster is trying to write the initialized X data at day 0 into <code>kvranges</code> in 10 days? And the <code>logs</code> contains all the modifications from day 0 through day 19?</p>\n<p>But if it works as it. Doesn\u2019t the cluster also need to keep the initialized X data for ten days? After all data has been written into the <code>kvranges</code>, then the cluster can safely discard the old data and apply mutation logs.</p>\n<p>And is the snapshot window only meaningful for once? Let\u2019s say if I want to restore the data at day 21. I will still have only one snapshot file and log files of 21*X sizes?</p>",
